## Agent conventions

This repo adopts the [agent-stack](https://github.com/<your-org>/agent-stack)
framework. The framework's `core/` docs (installed by the
init script under `docs/agents/`) carry the stack-agnostic
rules; the per-stack rules live in
[`docs/agents/addenda/`](docs/agents/addenda/). Per
[`core/laws.md § Tier-0 docs have a size ceiling`](docs/agents/laws.md),
this file must stay short; for full guidance, follow the
links below rather than inlining.

- Commit + branch policy:
  [`docs/agents/commit-and-branch.md`](docs/agents/commit-and-branch.md)
- Bug catalog + protocol:
  [`docs/agents/bug-patterns.md`](docs/agents/bug-patterns.md),
  [`docs/agents/issues/bug-template.md`](docs/agents/issues/bug-template.md)
- Feature protocol + slice discipline:
  [`docs/agents/feature-protocol.md`](docs/agents/feature-protocol.md),
  [`docs/agents/issues/feature-template.md`](docs/agents/issues/feature-template.md)
- Domain glossary: [CONTEXT.md](CONTEXT.md) — read
  end-to-end before any schema-touching or copy-writing work.
- [`CHANGELOG.md`](CHANGELOG.md) `[Unreleased]` block —
  update in the same commit as the change.

